# Study Notes - Parallel Architecture :Processes and Memory Coordination

# 1. Topic Overview

This chapter explains how modern DBMS systems use **parallel hardware** to improve performance.

Key idea:

> Modern servers have multiple CPUs/cores → DBMS must exploit this parallelism efficiently.

It introduces **different hardware architectures** and explains:

* how DBMS runs on them
* how memory is coordinated
* what trade-offs exist

This is important because:

* scalability depends on architecture
* performance bottlenecks shift (CPU → memory → network)
* real-world systems are built using these models

